<strong>Fletching tradition</strong>

Bows are wood; arrows are metal. The two ladders meet at the bow grip.

<strong>Arrows</strong>
Cut an arrowshaft from any wood log with a knife (left-click). Combine the shaft with a feather in the grid to make a headless arrow. Add any arrowhead (mithril, adamantite, runite, dragon, plus all vanilla tiers — see <a href="metals">Metals ladder</a>) to finish.

<strong>Bows</strong>
Cut an unstrung bow from a log of the named wood. Add a bowstring in the grid to finish. Bow wood ladder: common → oak → willow → maple → yew → magic. Each step is a meaningful stat increase.

<strong>Shortbow vs longbow</strong>
Shortbows draw fast (high rate of fire, low range). Longbows draw slow (lower rate, longer range and higher per-shot damage). Pair shortbow with mid-tier arrows for sustained DPS; pair longbow with dragon-tipped for burst.
